    "These clusters are substantially larger than the sets from the MISATO benchmark and do not necessarily originate from the same publication and the same experimental method within a set.",
    "The absolute correlations decreased for this second, more diverse benchmark (Supplementary Fig. 4).",
    "Still, we see the same trend as for the first benchmark with a better performance of the MISATO model including adaptability and QM features than the other approaches.",
    "Finally, consistent improvement of affinity prediction model accuracy upon inclusion of QM and dynamic features was observed for the entire curated set as well as selected subsets with high-confidence affinity values (Fig. 6 and Supplementary Figs.",
